# Neovim Configuration Project Structure

## Core Files
- [init.lua](mdc:init.lua) - Main entry point that bootstraps lazy.nvim and loads core modules
- [lua/set.lua](mdc:lua/set.lua) - Core Neovim settings and options
- [lua/remap.lua](mdc:lua/remap.lua) - Key mappings and shortcuts
- [lua/hades/lazy_init.lua](mdc:lua/hades/lazy_init.lua) - Lazy.nvim plugin configuration

## Plugin Organization
- Plugin specifications are located in `lua/plugins/` directory
- Each plugin has its own file (e.g., `treesitter.lua`, `telescope.lua`, `lsp.lua`)
- Plugin files return Lazy configuration tables
- Follow lowercase, hyphenated naming convention for plugin files

## Configuration Modules
- Core functionality modules are in `lua/` directory
- Plugin-specific utilities should be scoped near their specs
- Avoid global namespace pollution by keeping helpers modular

## Lock Files
- [lazy-lock.json](mdc:lazy-lock.json) - Pins plugin versions for reproducible installs
- Only update through Lazy commands, never hand-edit